			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">On the FoH site, I just read a thread where Absor says there will be a chat on 24 Nov to discuss the long-awaited upgrades to the melee system.  One of the purposes of this upgrade will be to bring the melee classes closer to the casting classes in terms of balance.  Most EQ players agree this is a long-needed change.
<br />

<br />
here is the link:
<br />
<a href="http://www.fohguild.org/forums/showthread.php?s=32af55c77d6b03da0b431f75c15f9f72&threadid=9588" target="_blank">http://www.fohguild.org/forums/showthread.php?s=32af55c77d6b03da0b431f75c15f9f72&threadid=9588</a>
<br />

<br />
In the meantime, there is the rumored expansion waiting in the background.  Lucy already has some new spells/AAs on Test that many assume are related to the new expansion.  So whether or not the level cap is raised in the new expansion, safe to assume casting classes will get some new toys to play with.  Whatever these new spells/AAs are, I assume SOE will combine them with the upcoming upgrades to melee classes to achieve balance in the future expansion.  
<br />

<br />
Here is what I would like to see for the expansion spells (yes I know yet another wishlist).  Instead of giving us a new DD nuke, AE rain, bolt, etc that does more damage with a better damage/mana ratio, I would like to see spells that combine damage with a secondary effect.  For example, we already have Manastorm, which is a rain spell with a manadrain as a secondary effect.  The problem with this spell is that it has a higher resist rate because there are two resist checks, one for the damage and one for the mana drain.  As a result Manastorm is a rarely used spell.  For the expansion, spells with secondary effects would not suffer this penalty.  There would only be one resist check.  
<br />

<br />
Here are examples of possible secondary effects for mage spells.  Each class would get secondary effects in line with the type of spells they can cast.
<br />

<br />
Shock line of spells
<br />

<br />
Most of our Conjuration direct damage spells are "Shock" spells.  We conjure pointed objects and fling them at our targets to inflict damage (ex. Black Steel summons an obsidian blade to cleave the target).  So lets assume these conjured objects damage some armor when they hit.  A secondary effect for the upgraded version of Black Steel could be an AC debuff (ex -50 AC).  The amount of direct damage the spell does remains the same as Black Steel.
<br />

<br />
Anti-summoned line of spells
<br />

<br />
For our anti-summoned line of spells, add in a short duration Stun component (ex 3 seconds).   The nature of these spells causes a momentary disruption in the magic that allows the summoned creature to exist outside their native plane.  In addition, when you get a crit casting Destroy Summoned, the mob makes a second resist check and if it fails, gets banished back to its home plane (similar to our current Banishment spell but the group gets EXP credit for the kill).
<br />

<br />
Bolt spells
<br />

<br />
Include a major knockback component that will interrupt spell casting mobs if timed right.
<br />

<br />
Evocation fire based spells
<br />

<br />
Add a minor DOT effect in addition to the primary damage from the nuke.  This would simulate the target catching on fire and taking additional damage for X number of seconds.  
<br />

<br />
Damage modifier against armor types.  
<br />

<br />
Our electricity based spells could do more damage against mobs wearing plate and chain armor while doing base damage against mobs with leather and cloth armor.  This would require each mob to have an associated armor type assigned to it (if they don't have one already).  Conversely, our fire based spells would do more damage against leather and cloth mobs and base damage to plate and chain mobs.  
<br />

<br />
Resist bonus/penalty based on armor types.  
<br />

<br />
Similar to the damage modifer.  For plate/chain wearing mobs, electricity based spells get a resist bonus while fire based spells get a penalty.  In other words, its easier to get an electricity based spell to land for full damage against a plate/chain mob.  Vice versa for leather/cloth wearing mobs.
<br />

<br />
These are ideas I came up with off the top of my head.  Some of them have been mentioned before by others.  Lot of speculation on other boards that future improvements to the game will be due to competition from World of Warcraft.  Read the home page of the FoH site to see Furor's update on how melee works in WoW.  Some pretty cool stuff planned for WoW.  Imitation is the highest form of flattery so safe to assume SOE might borrow some of Blizzard's ideas.   Purpose of this thread would be to give them other ideas on what changes we would like to see.
<br />

<br />
Kebkin</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
