				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Also from a PoP raiding mage perspective -- differentiate us from Wizzies.
<br />

<br />
Right now, wizzies have better burst ("burn it down") DPS and comparable total damage in boss fights. Why take a mage to a Time or LDoN raid if you can have a wizzie? Certianly why take a <span style="font-style: italic">second </span>mage? Mages are but a second- or third-rate damage dealer for high-end raid encounters.
<br />

<br />
Either pets for high-end encounters need to be made able to survive and significantly beefed up in DPS, or mages need to get some unique ability that provides the "I need another mage" impetus. I can't comment on Time encounters, but even for most elemental encounters, simply making mages masters of the long-haul burn isn't going to be enough -- the mobs don't last long.
<br />

<br />
Look at most any elemental or Time guild recruiting page -- "Only apply if you are a cleric or a hot-shit wizzy."</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
