			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm sure someone will slam me with the "don't paint us all in the corner like the conjurer YOU are" line but......
<br />

<br />
We are a conjuration class and upgrades should come mainly within that line.  IMO, if you want to be an evoker, be a wizard.  That's defining and differentiating.  In that regard:
<br />

<br />
(1) A new kind of pet.  I've brought out several ideas in the past but at this date in EQ we should start expanding on our core abilities in a creative way, and still stay firmly within the class parameters.  This new pet would have some hybrid ability or completely new ability having been summoned from some demi-plane or from a different plane all together.
<br />

<br />
(2) MS4.  I want it for the fun of it.  I want a pure melee pet.  I want its ability to be creative like "cleave" which delivers a critical on the mob.  Not to the extent of backstab but something that is fun and eye candy and that also acts as a '0' sec stun that can iterrupt casting.
<br />

<br />
(3) Fix the fire pet once and for all.  Remove root and aoe.  It's not wanted and keeps me from using the pet except for giggles or in very specialized situations.  I'd like to have more use for it.
<br />

<br />
(4) Focused Form:  As mentioned by someone else on this board, I'd like to have the ability to focus my pet further, further enhancing our pets' defense and offense.  This would require level 3 of all elemental forms first then an additional 9 points for the 'focused form'.  Once you hit the button it works like the other elemental forms but you gain something of each form and are then able to focus any summoned pet when in that form, which would stack with other focus items like DPoC.
<br />

<br />
(5) Elemental Affinity:  Three levels.  Decreases check against magic or fire by -5/-10/-15 for a cost of 3/6/9.  this doesn't make us wizards but does give us a little something against those mobs that ONLY wizards (or life taps) are landing firmly on.  Requires FoM3.  So you just simply can't waltz in and get it.  Will require a lot of work.
<br />

<br />
(6) Cold Damage Shield.  Same as what we already have but confers a cold buff equal to what our current fire shield does.  This further differentiates us without unbalancing us.  Just another tool in our tool box.
<br />

<br />
Those are the basics............<br />_________________<br />Sage Sarridon Soulcraver
<br />
Arch Convoker-Terris Thule</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
