				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Apply this rule to the summon pet checks.
<br />

<br />
Max = (amount of magicians in raid +1) divided by 2
<br />
pet-Roof = amount of players in raid - pets in raid
<br />

<br />
IF Roof &gt; 0 and amount of personal pets &lt; max
<br />
allow summon more pets
<br />

<br />
1 = 1 pet allowed
<br />
2 = 1.5 ~ 1 pet allowed
<br />
3 = 2 pets allowed
<br />
9 = 5 pets
<br />
19 = 10 pets 
<br />
but the roof would not allow that many pets... with 5 groups with 1 magician in each the magician would be allowed max 3 pets each, but only more than 1 if the raid has more than (3x5) 15 players (magicians included).
<br />

<br />
The numbers is examples and would need tweaking.
<br />

<br />
<img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
